<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>NOW() isn't NOW(). SqLite for example does not recognize this function. If you want to code database independent you have to have some mechanism in Zend_Db_Expr namespace that handles the most common functions in a database independent way.</p>

<pre class="highlight"><code>
$adapter = Zend_Db::factory(..);
$adapter-&gt;getExpression()-&gt;now();
</code></pre>

<p>Each expression should extend Zend_Db_Expr and lay inside a Zend_Db_Expr_Engine_* namespace for example. They also need a way to be serialized and deserialized so that they can be used in configuration files, constants or other places that define SQL without knowing about the adapter.</p>

